🧠 What Is Domain Modeling? (0–20 mins)
🔹 Simple Definition (No Jargon)

Domain modeling = understanding the business problem and representing it as objects, rules, and relationships in software.

In other words:

“Before writing code, understand what exists in the business world and how it behaves.”

🔹 What Is the “Domain” Here?

The domain is:

Digital Banking

So domain concepts are things like:

User

Account

Transaction

Balance

Transfer

Notification

These exist even if no software existed.

🔹 What Domain Modeling Is NOT

❌ Not writing controllers
❌ Not choosing Kafka vs REST
❌ Not database optimization
❌ Not UI design

Those come after the domain is clear.

🔹 Why Domain Modeling Is Critical
Without Domain Modeling

God classes (BankService)

Confusing APIs

Business rules scattered everywhere

Painful microservices split later

With Domain Modeling

Clean entities

Clear service boundaries

Business rules in the right place

Easy evolution to microservices

🔹 How to Do Domain Modeling (Practical Steps)
Step 1: Identify Nouns (Things)

Ask:

“What are the main things in the business?”

For banking:

User

Account

Transaction

Notification

These usually become entities.

Step 2: Identify Verbs (Actions)

Ask:

“What actions happen?”

Examples:

Create account

Transfer money

Credit / debit

Send notification

These usually become service methods.

Step 3: Identify Rules

Ask:

“What must ALWAYS be true?”

Examples:

Balance cannot be negative

Transaction must be atomic

Notifications must not block money transfer

These become business validations.

🔹 Banking Example (Very Important)

Real-world thinking:

A User owns one or more Accounts

Money lives in Account, not User

Transaction moves money between accounts

Notification just informs — it does not change money

👉 This thinking directly shapes your classes.

🔹 How Domain Modeling Helps System Design

Good domain model ⇒

Clear microservice boundaries

Correct data ownership

Better consistency decisions

Example:

Account Service owns balance

Transaction Service orchestrates transfer

Notification Service is async

🔹 Interview-Ready Explanation

“Domain modeling is the process of identifying core business entities, their relationships, and business rules before writing code. It ensures that the system structure mirrors real-world behavior and scales cleanly as the system grows.”

