📂 Folder Structure for Clean Architecture

(Day 3 – Pre-Coding Final Step)

⏱️ Time: 120–150 mins
🎯 Goal: Create a structure that works for

Monolith today

Microservices tomorrow

🔹 Core Principle (Memorize This)

Dependencies point inward

Domain → depends on nothing

Service → depends on domain

Controller → depends on service

Never the reverse.

🔹 High-Level Package Structure

We start as a modular monolith (BEST approach).

com.bankapp
 ├── account
 ├── transaction
 ├── user
 ├── notification
 └── shared


Each module is microservice-ready.

🔹 Inside Each Module (Clean Architecture)

Example: account

account
 ├── domain
 │    ├── Account.java
 │    ├── AccountStatus.java
 │    └── exception
 │         └── InsufficientBalanceException.java
 │
 ├── application
 │    └── AccountService.java
 │
 ├── infrastructure
 │    ├── AccountRepository.java
 │    └── JpaAccountRepository.java
 │
 └── web
      └── AccountController.java


🔥 This structure scales cleanly.

🔹 Layer Responsibilities (Clear & Strict)
📦 domain

Pure Java

Business rules

No Spring annotations

📦 application (Service Layer)

Use cases

@Transactional

Calls domain logic

📦 infrastructure

JPA entities

DB mappings

External integrations

📦 web

REST controllers

DTOs

Request validation

🔹 Why This Is Better Than Common Structures

❌ controller/service/repository only
→ Grows into chaos

✅ Domain-centric structure
→ Clear ownership
→ Easy microservice split

🔹 Transaction Module Example
transaction
 ├── domain
 │    ├── Transaction.java
 │    └── TransactionStatus.java
 ├── application
 │    └── TransactionService.java
 ├── infrastructure
 │    └── TransactionRepository.java
 └── web
      └── TransactionController.java

🔹 Shared Module (Be Careful)
shared
 ├── exception
 ├── event
 └── config


Rules:

No business logic

Only reusable utilities

Avoid dumping ground ❌

🔹 How This Converts to Microservices Later
account-service
transaction-service
notification-service
user-service


👉 Copy module → standalone service
👉 Minimal refactor
👉 Clean boundaries already exist

🔹 Interview-Ready Explanation

“I start with a modular monolith using Clean Architecture. Each domain module is independently deployable later as a microservice, which avoids premature distribution while keeping scalability.”

This is senior-level thinking 💎

